## TypeScript Rules

- Never use `any` — use `unknown` and narrow it, or define a proper type
- Always derive TypeScript types from Zod schemas using `z.infer<typeof schema>`
- Type all function return values explicitly
- Prefer discriminated unions over boolean flags

```typescript
// ✅ Good — type derived from schema
export type ReviewFields = z.infer<typeof reviewSchema>;

// ✅ Good — unknown narrowed
function handleError(error: unknown) {
  if (error instanceof Error) return error.message;
  return "Unexpected error";
}

// ❌ Bad
const handler = async (data: any) => { ... };
```

---

## File Exports

- One component per file
- Named exports for all components
- Default export only for Next.js pages and layouts

```typescript
// ✅ components/features/chat/ChatMessage.tsx
export function ChatMessage({ message }: ChatMessageProps) { ... }

// ✅ app/[locale]/(dashboard)/chat/page.tsx
export default function ChatPage() { ... }
```

---

## Code Quality Rules

**Blank lines between sections** — always leave a blank line after `"use client"`, imports, constants, and between logical sections inside a component or function.

**Comments before sections** — add a short, concise comment before each logical section inside a component body.

```typescript
// ✅ Good
"use client";

import { useChat } from "ai/react";

export default function ChatPage() {
  // Translation
  const t = useTranslations("chat");

  // State
  const [isStreaming, setIsStreaming] = useState(false);

  // AI Chat hook
  const { messages, input, handleSubmit } = useChat({ api: "/api/chat" });

  // Functions
  function handleKeyDown(e: KeyboardEvent) { ... }

  return <></>;
}
```

**No commented-out code** — remove all dead code.

**No `console.log`** — use `console.error` only for caught errors.

**No unused imports** — every import must be used.

**Stable keys in lists** — never use array index as key. Use stable IDs.

```typescript
// ✅ Good
messages.map((msg) => <ChatMessage key={msg.id} message={msg} />)

// ❌ Bad
messages.map((msg, index) => <ChatMessage key={index} message={msg} />)
```

---

## Import Order

```typescript
// 1. React / Next.js core
import { useState } from "react";

// 2. Third-party libraries
import { useChat } from "ai/react";
import { useTranslations } from "next-intl";

// 3. Internal aliases
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";
import { MENTOR_SYSTEM_PROMPT } from "@/lib/ai/prompts";

// 4. Relative
import { MessageBubble } from "./MessageBubble";
```

---

## Component Internal Order

```typescript
export default function MyComponent() {
  // Translation
  // Navigation
  // State
  // Ref
  // Context
  // Hooks (AI, auth, custom)
  // Queries
  // Mutations
  // Form & validation
  // Variables
  // Functions
  // Effects

  return <></>;
}
```
